^-|ht|c|cs||CP||fp||cp|8|AT|^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The reason you leave out the suit length part of Starting Points, when calculating adjusted HCP for the Rule of 20, is as follows. The Rule of 20 has 2 parts -- HCP and the length of your 2 longest suits. Adjusted HCP take care of the HCP part of the Rule of 20. The length of your 2 longest suits part already takes into account length points, so to include that when calculating the HCP part of the Rule of 20 would be double counting. |
