AT|

^B@2^*BMM: ^*NYou probably are questioning the differences. It is very simple. Bergen considers Aces and Kings under valued while Queens and Jacks (quacks) are over valued. Further, he subtracts points for dubious Singleton/Doubletons while he adds points for quality suits. Then he has the Adjust-3 in which he gives points to the hands rich in Aces and Tens while subtracts points when the hand is poor in those. Please use this |CP|1|AT|^*Htiny.cc/x6vpsw^*N|CP||AT| link for additional information on Bergen's hand evaluation.|
